<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>First Nations Report Spending</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.0.2/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.0.3/css/font-awesome.min.css">

</head>
<body>

	<div class = "container">
	<h1>First Nations Report Spending</h1>
	<form action = "/make-report" , method = "POST">
	<fieldset>
		<label for "fundProvided">Funding Provided: </label>
		<input type = "number" id = "fundProvided" name = "fundProvided" placeholder = "25000"/ required>
		<br>
		<label for "fundSpent">Funding Spent: </label>
		<input type = "number" id = "fundSpent" name = "fundSpent" placeholder = "20000"/ required>
		<br>
		<label for "fundRecovered">Funding to be Recovered (Funding provided minus funding spent): </label>
		<input type = "number" id = "fundRecovered" name = "fundRecovered" placeholder = "5000"/>

	</fieldset> <br>
	<fieldset>
		<p> Who administered home and community care services in your community in 2017-18? The Ministry of Health
		and Long-Term Care will use this information to understand the service delivery network in your community.
		<br>Check all that apply: </p>
		<input type="checkbox" name="adminDirect"/> Direct delivery by the community<br>
		<input type="checkbox" name="adminThirdParty" /> Third-party service delivery organization (please include the name below)<br>
		<input type="checkbox" name="adminCouncil" /> Tribal Council<br>
		<input type="checkbox" name="adminLHIN" /> Local Health Integration Network<br>
		<input type="checkbox" name="adminOther" /> Other (please specify below)<br>
		<input type = "text" id = "adminSpecify" name = "adminSpecify" placeholder = "Enter if you checked third party delivery organization or other" style = "width: 85%"/>
		<!-- I should probably think about the case where one checks both third party AND other :P -->
	</fieldset> <br>
	<fieldset>
		<p>Other Funding Sources... </p>
		<label for "fundNursing">Did the community also receive funding through the Homemaking and Nursing Services Act? </label>
		<input type="radio" name="fundNursing" value="on" checked> Yes
		<input type="radio" name="fundNursing" value="off"> No <br>

		<label for "fundGov">Did the community also receive or benefit from funding through the Government of Canada’s First Nations and Inuit Home
		and Community Care program? </label>
		<input type="radio" name="fundGov" value="on" checked> Yes
		<input type="radio" name="fundGov" value="off"> No <br>
	</fieldset> <br>
	<fieldset>
		<label for "numClients">Please outline how many clients the home and community care program served in 2017-2018 with all funding sources</label>
		<input type = "number" id = "numClients" name = "numClients" placeholder = "850" required/>
		<br>
		<label for "priorities">Please outline priorities for home and community care investment in the next five years</label> <br>
		<textarea id = "priorities" name = "priorities" placeholder = " " style = "width: 85%" rows = "5"/>
	</fieldset> <br>

	<fieldset>
		<p>Please indicate how the funding was spent in 2017-18.<br> Please check all that apply: </p>
		<input type="checkbox" name="useDirectFirstNations"/> Direct Services for home or community care and/or palliative care
		(directly employed by the First Nations)<br>
		<input type="checkbox" name="useDirectOther"/> Direct Services for home or community care and/or palliative and end-of-life care
		(provided by another organization)<br>
		<input type="checkbox" name="useTraining"/> Training, education<br>
		<input type="checkbox" name="useAdmin"/> Operational, oversight or administrative expensive<br>
		<input type="checkbox" name="useRecruit"/> Recruitment<br>
		<input type="checkbox" name="useSupplies"/> Supplies/equipment for clients/patients<br>
		<input type="checkbox" name="useOfficeSupplies"/> Office supplies/equipment/IT solutions for administering the home and
		community care program<br>
		<input type="checkbox" name="useTravel"/> Travel<br>

		<label for "useOther">Any other home and community care or palliative and end-of-care priorities: </label> <br>
		<textarea id = "useOther" name = "useOther" style = "width: 85%" rows = "5"/>
	</fieldset> <br>
	<fieldset>
		<label for "comments">Please provide any other comments: </label> <br>
		<textarea id = "comments" name = "comments" style = "width: 85%" rows = "5"/>
		<br>
		<input type="checkbox" name="approval" required/> Check if the above information is approved by the Chief or the Chief's delegated authority
		to approve reports to the ministry. <br>
	</fieldset> <br>

	<br>
	<input type = "submit" value = "Submit"/>
	<br>
	</form>
<br><br>
</div>
<!-- I could give this a seperate html page, and use include to add it in, just to modularize everything better. For now I'll just keep it here-->
	<div class = "container info">
		<h2><center> Information and notes: </center></h2>
		<br>
		<h4>Eligible areas of Expenditure</h4>
		<p>Funding is for home and community care, including palliative and end-of-life care, based on each First Nations community’s priorities.
		<br>Eligible direct and indirect expenditure areas are outlined below, based on the Home Care and Community Services Act.
		Implicit in this list are costs related to cultural and spiritual components of service delivery. </p>
		<br>
		<h4>Examples of Direct Services</h4>
		<u>Community Support Services</u>
		<ol>
			<li>Meal Services</li>
			<li>Transportation Services</li>
			<li>Caregiver support services</li>
			<li>Adult day programs</li>
			<li>Home maintenance and repair services</li>
			<li>Friendly visiting services</li>
			<li>Security checks or reassurance services</li>
			<li>Social or recreational services</li>
			<li>First Nations/Indigenous support</li>
			<li>Client intervention and assistance</li>
			<li>Emergency response</li>
			<li>Foot care</li>
			<li>Home help referral</li>
			<li>Independence training</li>
			<li>Palliative care education and consultation</li>
			<li>Psycho-geriatric consulting services related to Alzheimer disease and dementia</li>
			<li>Public education services relating to Alzheimer disease and dementia</li>
			<li>Services for persons with blindness/visual impairment</li>
			<li>Services for persons with deafness/congenital/acquired hearing loss</li>
		</ol>

	</div>
</body>


</html>
